HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 139
BY REPRESENTATIVE HILFERTY
A RESOLUTION
To commend Guy Williams, president of Gulf Coast Bank & Trust, for his assistance to the
Lakeview community in New Orleans following Hurricane Katrina.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Guy Williams for his work as president
of Gulf Coast Bank & Trust and to commend him for his assisting the Lakeview community
following Hurricane Katrina; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams made an exceptional personal effort to assist the
Lakeview neighborhood and its residents in the aftermath of Hurricane Katrina; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams provided much needed space for community meetings,
created a temporary office for the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association, and supported
fundraising efforts for local schools and charitable organizations; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams offered Gulf Coast Bank & Trust facilities and personnel
when the Lakeview community was in need; despite a lack of computers and functioning
systems, he opened the bank and ensured that residents were provided with immediate access
to financial relief; he also facilitated essential business and mortgage lending during the
crisis; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams and Gulf Coast Bank & Trust assisted the Lake
Pontchartrain Basin Foundation with the restoration of the New Canal Lighthouse, which
serves as the logo of the Lakeview Civic Improvement Association; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Williams displayed inspiring leadership by providing practical
assistance and deep emotional support to the community; he helped save lives in the wake
of an unprecedented disaster and exemplified true dedication to the residents of Lakeview
and the citizens of the city of New Orleans; and
